_field_real.name: mass scale#scales the mass of each rigid body. If you leave this field as 0, then it will be calculated from the total mass below.

mass#override total mass of all rigid bodies. Note that this will NOT be the mass of the object if not all rigid bodies are present (for example if you are using permutations) If you set a mass scale above, this field is unused.
low freq. deactivation scale#0 is default (1). LESS than 1 deactivates less aggressively. GREATER than 1 is more agressive.
high freq. deactivation scale#0 is default (1). LESS than 1 deactivates less aggressively. GREATER than 1 is more agressive.
custom shape radius!#0 defaults to .016. This field is intentionally hidden because we should only alter this for very special situations. Lower number == lower performance
maximum penetration depth scale#0 is default (1). for objects that are prone to falling through the world we can reduce this number at the cost of performance
minimum force#0 defaults to maximum force. In general you should leave this alone unless working on ragdolls or something like them
minimum force#0 defaults to maximum force. In general you should leave this alone unless working on ragdolls or something like them
proportion recover vel#fraction of recover velocity used. 0 defaults to 1
consant recover vel#velocity used to recover when errors happen. in degress per second

_field_block.name: phantom types

_field_real.name: brittle timer:seconds#objects in this phantom volume will be set to brittle collision damage for this amount of time.

_field_string_id.name: marker name#you don't need this if you're just generating effects. If empty it defaults to the up of the object
alignment marker name#you don't need this if you're just generating effects. If empty it defaults to "marker name"

_field_block._field_explanation: 0 - means do nothing CENTER: motion towards marker position AXIS: motion towards marker axis, such that object is on the axis DIRECTION: motion along marker direction

_field_real.name: hookes law e#0 if you don't want this to behave like spring. 1 is a good starting point if you do.
linear dead radius#radius from linear motion origin in which acceleration is dead.
orbit acc#negative values spin the opposite direction from positive ones

_field_block._field_explanation: 0 - means do nothing ALIGNMENT: algin objects in the phantom with the marker SPIN: spin the object about the marker axis

_field_real.name: alignment hookes law e#0 if you don't want this to behave like spring. 1 is a good starting point if you do.

item.Name: is physical child#this constraint will only be created when this object is a child of another physical object (turrets on vehicles for example)
is rigid#this constraint makes the edge rigid until it is loosened by damage
disable effects#this constraint will not generate impact effects
not created automatically#this flag is used for special systems that need to create constraints dynamically

_field_real.name: friction#0 is the default (takes what it was set in max) anything else overrides that value

_field_string_id.name: node a material#if you don't fill this out we will pluck the material from the first primitive, of the first rigid body attached to node a
node b material#if you don't fill this out we will pluck the material from the first primitive, of the first rigid body attached to node b, if node b is none we use whatever material a has

infinite intertia tensor#rigid body will never have angular velocity

explicit mass#the mass is explicit, and not computed based on volume and density
absolute center of mass#the 'center of mass offset' is relative to the pivot and not to the computed center
force keyframed#rigid body is always keyframed and can't be overriden to dynamic or fixed
force not cut NavMesh#this rigid body will not generate a cutting silhouette
